ðŸ‘‰ REST API - (Representational State Transfer API)

It is allows communication between systems over HTTP using standard methods like GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE.


ðŸ‘‰ Key Features :

---   Stateless : Each request is independent.
---   Client-Server : UI and backend are separate.
---   Uniform Interface : Consistent endpoints and methods.
---   Cacheable : Supports caching for faster responses.
---   Layered System : Intermediaries like load balancers are allowed.
---   Resource Representation : Data in JSON or XML format.


ðŸ‘‰ Working Process :

---   Client Request : Sends an HTTP request (GET, POST, etc.) to an endpoint.
---   Server Processing : Processes the request and interacts with the database.
---   Response : Server returns data with an HTTP status code.


-->>   Example :   <<--

ðŸ‘‰ GET : https://api.example.com/books/1

Response :
-->>   { "id": 1, "title": "RESTful API", "author": "John Doe" }


ðŸ‘‰ POST : https://api.example.com/books

-->>   Body :
{ "title": "New Book", "author": "Jane Smith" }


